Citations
Date: 0/0/1964
Source: Practical Guide to Handling Dogs and Stock
Author: MILLS ET AL
Vol / Page: 33
Edition:
Quote: You must guard against what is known as 'crossing his head' which is going out on one side and then at some stage crossing over, to finish up by heading his sheep from the opposite side from which he started.
Notes:

