Quote: crosshead (n or v): a fault made by a heading dog when he begins his cast out to one side and then switches to the other. [crosshead, cross one's head]
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1971
Source: Ten Thousand Dogs
Author: NEWTON
Vol / Page: 168
Edition:
Quote: (Glossary) <i>Cross-head</i>: A dog usually heads on one predetermined side. If after having started on that side he changes direction and heads on the other this is `cross-heading'.
Notes:

